The paper deals with entropy computations and inequalities involving random variables, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Gaussian distributions and sub-Gaussian decay suggests a connection to probability theory and statistical learning (cs.LG). The mention of bit reset operations and sharpness of results suggests a possible connection to computational complexity (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.ITP).
